This package contains source code for a shared memory, memory allocator.
Multiple processes can now use usmalloc, uscalloc, usrealloc, and usfree
(and more) to allocate and free memory from a shared memory pool.

1. This package is intended for Linux-based operating systems.

2. To build:  make
   The result should be two header files, a library file (usarena.a), and
   an example program (called: "example").
